President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of West Virginia due to a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred in December 2009. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and emergency protective measures. Regis Leo Phelan has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made later based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.